The paper discusses the design of erasure codes for distributed storage systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also addresses the network and computing load distribution, which is related to System and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents a real implementation and benchmarks its performance, which is related to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
